name: Lt. Governor David Toland
tweet: If you attended one of these events or remember my visit, let me know! We covered a lot of ground in 2019, and I want to hear from everyone. The first thread will be posted tomorrow!

name: Lt. Governor David Toland
tweet: With the end of the year approaching, I want to reflect on my first year as Secretary and my experiences traveling across the state. Over the next few days, I’ll be posting threads on some of the biggest trips I’ve gone on. I’m calling it #TolandTravels2019.

name: Lt. Governor David Toland
tweet: I do a lot of things, but one of the most important things I do is get out and visit people and places across Kansas that haven’t been visited in far too long.

name: Lt. Governor David Toland
tweet: When I was at Dighton Buzz earlier this year, an 11-year-old boy named Charlie asked me if I do anything but travel around the state and talk to people. It was a good question.

name: Lt. Governor David Toland
tweet: Pleased to support continued growth of Hess Services in Ellis County. Great celebration of partnerships led by @JerryMoran along with state and local officials who were instrumental in getting the NW Corridor project underway.   @RickBillinger @WasingerBarbara @Waymaster4house  https://t.co/pJcbxemI2B

name: Lt. Governor David Toland
tweet: My blog discusses how @KansasCommerce can help Kansas companies reach new markets. It includes the launch of a new program, announcement of new leadership for our International Division and opening of applications for 2020 Governor’s Exporter of the Year.  https://t.co/zNtmZEo58K

name: Lt. Governor David Toland
tweet: Today is @KansasCommerce's Holiday Party! These guys have helped secure more than 13,000 new jobs and $1.3 BILLION (!) in capital investment for our state this year. They've definitely earned the right to celebrate. Happy Holidays from a very grateful Secretary!  https://t.co/SYxDeOG0vO

name: Lt. Governor David Toland
tweet: Attended today's meeting of the Governor's Military Council. Kansas' sizeable military presence has a massive positive impact on the state's economy. Our military partners are vital to our state!  https://t.co/42QC45iFXF

name: Lt. Governor David Toland
tweet: Paid a surprise visit to our team at the Emporia Workforce Center today! Workforce visits are one of the best parts of this job. These folks work so hard for Kansas workers and businesses and I love getting to hear what’s happening in all our communities. @SEKWORKS  https://t.co/N1vktde3dr

name: Lt. Governor David Toland
tweet: I could not be more excited to join this incredible group of community leaders for our first @MainStreetKS Roundtable meeting today in Emporia. So many communities have told us how much they've missed this program, and we are so proud to be bringing it back. #KansasMainStreet  https://t.co/SFX6gTTyJQ

name: Lt. Governor David Toland
tweet: Stopped into the Workforce Services Holiday Luncheon today here in the Secretary's Office. These guys work so hard and the work they do for the people and businesses of our state is incredible. Happy Holidays to @KansasWorkforce across the state, and thanks for all you do!  https://t.co/vwfwsjIIZl

name: Lt. Governor David Toland
tweet: Enjoyed this morning’s town hall in Leawood where I got to talk about @kansasgrowth, @KansasCommerce and the future of our state’s economy. Big thanks to Rep. @Kessinger4KS and Sen. @JohnSkubal for the invitation!  https://t.co/FWqx7vFxkg

name: Lt. Governor David Toland
tweet: The economic impact and jobs created by the #travel industry in KS are significant. name: Lt. Governor David Toland
tweet: This morning, I arrived at the intersection of creative and commerce with @CenturionsKC. We had a great discussion on how the arts can fuel #ecodevo and how diversity and inclusion help build strong, vibrant communities. Also, check out @TheArtsAsylumKC - such a cool venue!  https://t.co/6ZqttYWAlF

name: Lt. Governor David Toland
tweet: Businesses are the foundation of our economy, and I'm grateful to the #kansasgrowth business council for joining us today in Topeka to talk about how we continue to move Kansas forward. Not surprisingly, talent and workforce development were strong themes in today's discussion.

name: Lt. Governor David Toland
tweet: Atchison is an amazing Kansas community and I have made a lot of friends there the past few years. Big thanks to local leaders like @justprego and partners like @networkkansas for showing what rural revitalization looks like in practice. A great read!

name: Lt. Governor David Toland
tweet: This Thanksgiving, I’m thankful for our state’s business community, the hardworking people of KS, our eco devo and community partners, and our amazing team at @KansasCommerce. And it’s a joy to serve the state I love. Happy Thanksgiving, everyone!

name: Lt. Governor David Toland
tweet: From all of us at @KansasCommerce, Happy Thanksgiving! And, as you start your holiday shopping, don't forget to shop small and local in Kansas.  https://t.co/NAQfDj0uBh

name: Lt. Governor David Toland
tweet: Had a great time @LawrenceRotary today. Great discussion about the future of @KansasCommerce and the important role of quality of life in economic development. Grateful to have been invited! @lawrenceks  https://t.co/wojCwAYzCK

name: Lt. Governor David Toland
tweet: One month ago tonight, I delivered the Anderson Chandler Lecture at @KUbschool. My blog shares a video of my remarks about the “Free State Free Thinkers” who built a legacy of innovation that still guides our state today.  https://t.co/VI8576GWVD

name: Lt. Governor David Toland
tweet: Tonight, I spoke to the World Trade Council of Wichita. Enjoyed the opportunity to discuss Kansas' role in the global economy and how @KansasCommerce can support firms in engaging new markets and selling their products all around the world.  https://t.co/HPMHG8AkNP

name: Lt. Governor David Toland
tweet: Had a great time at the @networkkansas #StartupGrind this evening! NetWork Kansas does a great job for our state’s entrepreneurs and we’re glad to be their partner! @EPedersenKS @SteveRadley3  https://t.co/AlXJ8113Jd

name: Lt. Governor David Toland
tweet: Absolutely thrilled to join @GovLauraKelly at the groundbreaking for the Sports of the World Complex in Garden City. This is the first STAR Bond project I approved as Secretary and it shows the Kelly Administration’s commitment to strengthening rural Kansas.  https://t.co/AJunQJxcxV

name: Lt. Governor David Toland
tweet: It's #NationalApprenticeshipWeek! Registered Apprenticeships allow Kansans to receive paid training along their pathway to a good job in our state. My blog shares more about innovative partnerships that help prepare Kansans for jobs today and tomorrow.  https://t.co/EYPNi0HeoM

name: Lt. Governor David Toland
tweet: I spoke at the Rural Independent Innovators Conference in #DodgeCity. My closing remarks focused on fostering the spirit of innovation that helped our ancestors carve out a life for themselves here. We must create an ecosystem to support & spark innovation through @KansasGrowth.  https://t.co/8S324YHIHX

name: Lt. Governor David Toland
tweet: Taking in some Kansas history at a great attraction in #DodgeCity, the @BootHillMuseum! I enjoyed checking out this STAR Bond project and touring the new facility opening in May! A great use of STAR Bonds!  https://t.co/mGpChZyWAp

name: Lt. Governor David Toland
tweet: His commitment and dedication to our state is to be commended, and his life is to be honored. My deepest condolences to Mr. Chandler's family and friends and the many people across the state who were touched by his legacy.

name: Lt. Governor David Toland
tweet: Just last week, I was privileged to speak at the Anderson Chandler Lecture Series at @KUbschool. The main message in my presentation was that Kansas was a state built by men and women with big ideas – innovators, risk takers, free thinkers. Anderson Chandler was one of those men.  https://t.co/wIrKBbffiz

name: Lt. Governor David Toland
